  "text": "If a graph H embeds in CRG K then a large enough graph that is approximated by K will have an induced copy of H. This is stated and proven more formally in Section 4 of [CITATION_1] . However, the main idea is that for any large graph in a hereditary property H = H∈F (H ) Forb(H), the CRG K that approximates the graph satisfies the property that H → K for all H ∈ F (H ). We denote K (H ) to be the subset of CRGs K such that no forbidden graph maps into K. Formally, K (H ) = {K : H → K, ∀H ∈ F (H )}.",
